reviews.text: I give this hotel high marks for location. Excellent for being near the water and walking the streets. Breakfast buffet is excellent. Rooms are clean, not spacious, but functional. Large lobby. I would definitely stay here again for the location alone.

Very nice and clean hotel. But you have to wait long time for elevator. Lobby is quite spacious rooms are clean and noise proof. Location is perfect just 2 steps from metro and close to Harbour. Staff very kibd always at your disposal. Entrance could be better marked.

What a great Hotel fantastic l location to get anywhere K2 bus outside brilliant for the station and connecting trains.  Ashley road where the pubs and restaurants are just over the road as well as all the shopping centres for all the world known brands.  Fantastic gym swimming pool outdoor area where you can  watch the sky show from the fourth floor.  Booked this hotel after seeing the reviews and am so glad we stayed here.   Rooms where fantastic are all the fruit.  Definitely come back here again.  Photo view from room

The interior is nice and rooms also has a very good view if you take a harbour view room.
But the time when I stayed the hotel was under renovation so had some difficulties going to and fro for a trip.
Overall, it is very good, especially the swimming pool.
Beautiful rooms and perfectly located. About one block from Nathan road, the ferry building, and MTR station. Very nice pools and workout facility. Great value.

1881ヘリテージの最上段には、1880年代初頭に、ヴィクトリア・コロニアル調と新古典派を組み合わせた設計で建築された旧海上警察本部の主要建築物があり、今はホテルとして20部屋ほど稼働しています。

内部には海賊や密輸業者が収監されていた独房があり、高床式のため、空調設備のない時代にも建物はなかなかの涼を保っていました。

建物の中庭にある独房の檻ではかつてハトが飼育され、ラジオが普及する以前の船舶と海岸との連絡役として、港の船にメッセージを届けていたそうです。

reviews.text: Let’s say you definitely pay for the experience as well as the name. As for the hotel, it was an amazing experience. Great room, great service, great location. Tea was another story. I’m vegetarian so they had to change the menu which was... interesting. Bread with cheese. Felt like I was in middle school and forgot to bring my lunch again. The helicopter experience on the other hand was an amazing experience. One I’ll never forget! This, to me, is a must when you visit Hong Kong.
Very much embedding the spirit of 5 stars hotel. I loved my short weekend in this hotel. Wonderful view on the harbour.
Iconic establishment.  Most amazing decor and dining experiences.  The ride from the airport in a Rolls-Royce phantom was pretty special.

If you are looking for one of the best hotels in Hong Kong, you are on the right place. Clean rooms, big rooms and beds, excellent hotel staff. All 5 stars deserved indeed!!! If you want Rolls Royce ride... No problem! Just perfect vacation in Hong Kong!

The service here was impeccable...our high tea was bit of a hit and a miss. Some of the food wasnt very flavorful and felt a bit dried out as they were prepared hours beforehand. The facilities were very clean and the high tea is great for wet day timetable or just to hide from the heat.
